<div id="review_16876326" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/16876326" />
    <a title="Drew J" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/961147-drew-j"><img alt="Drew J" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1204520128p2/961147.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/16876326?book_show_action=true">Mar 02, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Drew J" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Drew J" href="/user/show/961147-drew-j">Drew J</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">immature Christians</span></div>

          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Drew by: </span>
      everyone and their mama
  </div>


    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer16876326" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16245521193377796995">I think I&apos;m the only one in the world who hated this book. It annoyed the crap out of me. It lays out a canned formula to live. Turn-off for me.</span>
